	Disambiguation:
	 - "id": The Entity ID of your archetype.
	 - "PackIndex": Used to specify AbilityToComputePrice of the respective Item Pack this item is part of (in server_archetypes). More info above at the "PACK INDEX AND PRICING" chapter.
	 - "TypeId": The Item Type of this item. Alternatively, think of it as the category of item. You can find Item Type IDs for each... kind of item (color/sticker/interior/rim etc) below!
	 - "Type": CRC32 hash of the name of the Type ID, for example: color type 65CEBC8E would link to "_root.$Official_f", and subsequently it's color type entity in archetypes. [Inconsequential to TCU Server]
	 - "Level": Level of the item, ranging from 1 to 50. If you want to set the item level above 50, use:
	 - "CAULevel": Must match "Level" until level 50. After 50 it can go higher.
	 - "WhiteLevel": Worth of the item based on it's level and quality. More in-depth explanation at the start of this file.
	 - "ModelID": Model ID of the car this item is for exclusively. Use "FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF" (which is -1 as a signed 64 bit integer) to make it universal for all cars.
	 - "DressID": Same as Model ID but for the dress (spec) of the car. I believe using "FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF" would also make it universal.
	 - "QualityID": ID of the quality of this item (Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum). Quality IDs can be found below.
	 - "SlotID": ID of the car part slot that this item goes into. Slot IDs can be found below.
	
